Unity Scraps Runtime Fee
------------------------

From Reuters ( https://www.reuters.com/technology/unity-software-scraps-run=
time-fee-pricing-policy-introduces-price-hikes-2024-09-12/ ) :

Unity Software is abandoning its =E2=80=9Cruntime fee=E2=80=9D pricing poli=
cy, nearly a year after its announcement sparked considerable backlash from=
 the videogame developer community. The maker of the Unity Engine software =
said in a blog post on Thursday that it will revert to its =E2=80=9Cexistin=
g seat-based subscription model for all gaming customers=E2=80=9D and imple=
ment price increases for its Unity Pro and Unity Enterprise subscriptions. =
Shares of the company were up around 7% in afternoon trading.

The blog post ( https://unity.com/blog/unity-is-canceling-the-runtime-fee )=
 announcing the change was published by new CEO Matt Bromberg:

After deep consultation with our community, customers, and partners, we=E2=
=80=99ve made the decision to cancel the Runtime Fee for our games customer=
s, effective immediately. Non-gaming Industry customers are not impacted by=
 this modification.

Over the last 20 years, we=E2=80=99ve partnered with brilliant designers an=
d developers, artists and engineers, publishers and platforms, to build a w=
orld where great games could be built by anyone, for everyone. We called it=
 =E2=80=9Cdemocratizing game development,=E2=80=9D and it remains our core =
mission today.

However, we can=E2=80=99t pursue that mission in conflict with our customer=
s; at its heart, it must be a partnership built on trust. I=E2=80=99ve been=
 able to connect with many of you over the last three months, and I=E2=80=
=99ve heard time and time again that you want a strong Unity, and understan=
d that price increases are a necessary part of what enables us to invest in=
 moving gaming forward. But those increases needn=E2=80=99t come in a novel=
 and controversial new form.

